libotf
------------------------------------------
The library "libotf" provides the following facilites.

    * Read Open Type Layout Tables from OTF file. Currently these tables are
      supported; head, name, cmap, GDEF, GSUB, and GPOS.
    * Convert a Unicode character sequence to a glyph code sequence by using
      the above tables.

The combination of libotf and the FreeType library (Ver.2) realizes CTL
(complex text layout) by OpenType fonts.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.5-1
  libfreetype6-2.3.12-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3
  libX11_6-1.3.3-1
  libXaw7-1.0.7-1
  libXt6-1.0.8-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.65-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-10
  binutils-2.20.51-2
  cygport-0.9.85-1
  gawk-3.1.8-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  libtool-2.2.7a-15
  make-3.81-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.m17n.org/libotf/

Canonical download:
  http://www.m17n.org/libotf/libotf-0.9.11.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libotf-0.9.11-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libotf-0.9.11-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libotf-0.9.11-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libotf-0.9.11-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libotf0-0.9.11-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libotf-devel-0.9.11-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libotf)
  /usr/bin/otfdump.exe
  /usr/bin/otflist.exe
  /usr/bin/otftobdf.exe
  /usr/bin/otfview.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libotf.README
  /usr/share/doc/libotf/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libotf/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libotf/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libotf/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/libotf/README

(libotf0)
  /usr/bin/cygotf-0.dll

(libotf-devel)
  /usr/bin/libotf-config
  /usr/include/otf.h
  /usr/lib/libotf.a
  /usr/lib/libotf.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libotf.la
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libotf.pc

